oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Pete Seeger performing at Highlander
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Pete Seeger performing on banjo in the Highlander Folk School library. Written on verso: "Pete Seeger - one of most rabid commies."

While undated, this photograph was probably taken at Seeger's performance for Highlander's 25th Anniversary in 1957. Previously acquainted, Myles Horton invited legendary folk singer Pete Seeger to perform for the anniversary and marked the first time that Seeger met Martin Luther King Jr., Rosa Parks, and Ralph Abernathy.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Seeger, Pete, 1919-2014; Highlander Folk School (Monteagle, Tenn.)
